# Speech Adventure — Environment Variables Template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# .env.local is git-ignored (.env* pattern in .gitignore).
# This file (.env.example) is safe to commit — it contains ONLY placeholders.
#
# How to get Supabase values:
#   1. Create a project at https://app.supabase.com
#   2. Go to Project Settings → API
#   3. Copy "Project URL" → NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#   4. Copy "anon public" key → NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Storage Provider ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Controls which repository backend the app uses.
# Allowed values: local | supabase | hybrid
# Default (when unset): local
#
# - "local"    → all data in browser localStorage (default, no Supabase needed)
# - "supabase" → all data in Supabase (requires URL + KEY + user auth session)
# - "hybrid"   → Supabase primary, localStorage fallback (Phase 3+ target)
#
# Keep "local" until:
#   a) Supabase credentials are real (not placeholder)
#   b) Data has been migrated (Phase 30+)
NEXT_PUBLIC_STORAGE_PROVIDER=local

# ── Supabase Project ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for Supabase Auth and cloud storage (any provider other than "local")
# Leave as placeholder to run in localStorage-only mode.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here
